    {
      "question": "If one root of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 7x + m = 0$ is $4$, then the other root is",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the roots be $\\alpha$ and $\\beta$. Given $\\alpha = 4$.",
          "Sum of roots $\\alpha + \\beta = -b/a = 7$.",
          "Substitute $\\alpha = 4$: $4 + \\beta = 7$.",
          "Solve for $\\beta$: $\\beta = 3$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\alpha + \\beta = -(-7)/1 = 7 \\ 4 + \\beta = 7 \\ \\beta = 3"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "Roots of quadratic equation",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
      "options": [
        "(A) 7",
        "(B) 4",
        "(C) 3",
        "(D) 1"
      ],
